This paper discusses the performance analysis of a virtualized network that supports Internet of Things (IoT) services. The paper focuses on Network Function Virtualization (NFV) and Multi-access Edge Computing (MEC) which are related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses queueing models and stochastic models for performance analysis, which are related to operations research and optimization. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses analytical expressions and decision making, which are related to information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.PF (Performance) are also possible categories.
